{"ts":"2026-05-28T11:41:13.721Z","host":"Kash-MBA-M1-16GB","mode":"loop","item":"**Daemon broken: `_run_status_hook` is called but never defined** in `bin/backlog-agent`. Commit `ea44e7b` dropped the function definition during a refactor — the 3 call sites remain but every tick aborts (exit 127) at the status-hook step, so no `backlog-agent-status` commits are pushed and all `[~]` items stall. Fix: re-add the function as `_run_status_hook() { [[ -n \"$HOOK\" ]] && node \"$HOOK\" --item \"$1\" --exit-code \"$2\" --mode \"$3\" --pre-head \"$4\" --pulled \"$5\" >> \"$LOG_FILE\" 2>&1 || true; }`.","exit_code":1,"duration_ms":783,"tokens":0,"tokens_breakdown":{"input":0,"output":0,"cache_creation":0,"cache_read":0},"num_turns":1,"session_id":"c243194b-788f-4f74-bdca-07ba9c913293","work_commit":"0c0cdd5","pulled":2}
